2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"bp\">←</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">one_mul</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">exact</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">mul_le_mul_of_nonpos_right</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rfl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">le_of_lt</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">hb</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">have</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">4</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≤</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">le_trans</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">add_le_add</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">le_rfl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">this</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">exact</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">le_trans</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rfl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">this</span>\n</code></pre></div><br>\n</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>This proof does not follow the format the book teaches</p>",
